# Armors

      STR_EXOSUIT_UC: "EXOSUIT"
      STR_EXOSUIT_UFOPEDIA: "Powerful augmented exo-skeleton, reinforced with Alien Alloys. Increases the resistance and speed of the user, with improved damage protection. Capable of surface and underwater operations"
      STR_EXOSUIT_INTEL: "Exosuit Intel"
      STR_EXOSUIT_INTEL_UFOPEDIA: "The Elerium Shortages meant most Power Suits and Flying Suits armors couldn't be regularly used. The need of protection for assault troops pushed the development of the Exo-skeleton Armored Suit, or 'Exosuit' for short. An augmented external frame with Alloys plates protects the user and vastly improves the physical resistance and abilities, albeit without the full armor rating of the First War armored units."
      STR_EXOSUIT_ARMOR_CORPSE: "Corpse"
      STR_WRECKED_EXOSUIT_ARMOR: "Wrecked Exosuit"
      STR_EXOSUIT_ARMOR: "Exosuit"

      STR_PERSONAL_ARMOR_BROWN_UC: "Personal Armor (Desert)"
      STR_DUMMY_PERSONAL_ARMOR: "PERSONAL ARMOR"
      STR_PERSONAL_ARMOR_UFOPEDIA: "Since the 2010s, conventional-looking Personal Armors replaced the old ones. FAST-type helmets are the norm in armed forces all over the world. Our operatives will be automatically equipped with a standard body armor in Land missions. "
      STR_PERSONAL_ARMOR_BROWN_CORPSE: "Corpse"
      STR_PERSONAL_ARMOR_GREEN_UC: "Personal Armor (Forest)"
      STR_PERSONAL_ARMOR_GREEN_CORPSE: "Corpse"
      STR_PERSONAL_ARMOR_GRAY_UC: "Personal Armor (Urban)"
      STR_PERSONAL_ARMOR_GRAY_CORPSE: "Corpse"

      STR_LUNG: "Aqualung"
      STR_LUNG_I: "AQUALUNG"
      STR_LUNG_UFOPEDIA: "Standart issue diving suit with aqualung. While provides no additional protection, allows relative freely movement underwater due to some fatigue."
